HEADWORD: Pelota
<hw>Pe*lo"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp., lit.,
ball.]</ety> <def>A Basque, Spanish, and Spanish-American game played in
a court, in which a ball is struck with a wickerwork racket.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> jai alai.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

